registerInputStream

public void registerInputStream(InputStream inputStream)
Sub-classes can use this method to register an InputStream created by a StatelessChannel. Once registered, the InputStream can be cancelled by calling the cancel method.

A weak reference to the InputStream is maintained here, so that when the user code disposes this InputStream it will automatically be un-registered.

See Also:
cancel()

registerOutputStream

public void registerOutputStream(OutputStream outputStream)
Sub-classes can use this method to register an OutputStream created by a StatelessChannel. Once registered, the OutputStream can be cancelled by calling the cancel method.

A weak reference to the OutputStream is maintained here, so that when user the user code disposes the OutputStream it will automatically be un-registered.
